# API README Quality Guardrails

## Content Rules

- **English only** — no Korean, Chinese, Japanese, or other non-English text
- **No company names** — no "Mercor", "Turing", or other company references (open source ready)
- **No internal jargon** — explain concepts clearly for external contributors

## Test Table Rules

- **Exceptions only** — NEVER list PASS tests in any README table. Only SKIP and FAIL appear.
- **Simulation Limitations table** — `| Limitation | Skipped Tests |` — one row per limitation, accepted simplifications, no TODO needed
- **Cross-Function Needs Resolution table** — `| Test | Functions Involved | Failing Function | Resolution |` — only populated when failures exist; empty/dummy when all pass
- **Run tests before writing** — always run `pytest -v` to get live status, never guess

## Required Sections

Every API README must include:
1. Overview and summary tables
2. Database structure
3. Module/model architecture
4. Unit Tests section (purpose + categories)
5. Scenario Tests section (purpose + 3 categories)
6. Simulation Limitations (exceptions-only: limitation → skipped tests)
7. Cross-Function Tests — Needs Resolution (exceptions-only: failures only, dummy when clean)
8. Validation Infrastructure
9. How to Run Tests (with actual commands)

## Scalability

- If README exceeds ~300 lines, shorten the API overview, not the testing section
- Simulation Limitations: one row per limitation (not per test), skipped tests comma-separated
- Cross-Function Needs Resolution: empty table when all tests pass
- PASS tests are verified by running `pytest -v`, not by documenting them
